From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 28 Feb 2026 13:27:50 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] pwm: sky1: fix NULL dereference in suspend

sky1_pwm_suspend() calls dev_get_drvdata() to retrieve the pwm_chip,
but probe never called platform_set_drvdata().  This causes a NULL
pointer dereference at offset 0x78 (pwmchip_get_drvdata) when the
system enters suspend.

Add the missing platform_set_drvdata() call in probe.
---
 drivers/pwm/pwm-sky1.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/pwm/pwm-sky1.c b/drivers/pwm/pwm-sky1.c
index 7e071547c40b6..df878748d7897 100644
--- a/drivers/pwm/pwm-sky1.c
+++ b/drivers/pwm/pwm-sky1.c
@@ -210,6 +210,7 @@ static int pwm_sky1_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return PTR_ERR(sky1->mmio_base);
 
 	chip->ops = &pwm_sky1_ops;
+	platform_set_drvdata(pdev, chip);
 
 	ret = pwm_sky1_clk_prepare_enable(sky1);
 	if (ret)
